"""
MLB Home Run Model — Phase 2  |  FanDuel DFS HR Contest Optimizer
===================================================================

QUICK START
-----------
  python mlb_hr_model.py                    # Run today's slate
  python mlb_hr_model.py --refresh-odds     # Force fresh HR odds (use if odds look stale)
  python mlb_hr_model.py --refresh-stats    # Force fresh Statcast/FanGraphs pitcher+batter data
  python mlb_hr_model.py --help             # Full command reference

ALL COMMANDS
------------
  --date YYYY-MM-DD    Score a specific date (historical or upcoming)
                         python mlb_hr_model.py --date 2026-04-15
                         python mlb_hr_model.py --date 04/15/2026
  --top N              Show top N players instead of default 25
                         python mlb_hr_model.py --top 20
  --out FILENAME       Custom output Excel filename
                         python mlb_hr_model.py --out sunday_picks.xlsx
  --refresh-odds       Delete today's odds cache and re-fetch from SGO + OddsAPI
                         Use when HR odds show N/A or you want updated lines
                         (costs 2 SGO tokens out of your 2500/month)

  Flags can be combined:
    python mlb_hr_model.py --refresh-odds --top 20
    python mlb_hr_model.py --date 2026-04-15 --top 20 --out apr15.xlsx

DATA SOURCES  (priority order)
-------------------------------
  1. FantasyLabs (FL)       FantasyLabsMLB.xlsm — lineups, batting order, implied
                            runs, salary, weather. Must be saved in HR Models folder.
  2. SportsGameOdds (SGO)   Primary odds source. 2500 tokens/month. Fetches anytime
                            HR ou-over lines; falls back to first-HR-scorer lines if
                            a player has no anytime HR prop posted yet.
  3. OddsAPI                Fallback odds for any player SGO missed. DraftKings +
                            FanDuel books only. ~240 credits/day.
  4. Baseball Savant        Statcast: Barrel%, HardHit%, EV, xSLG, SweetSpot%.
                            Cached 24h in .stat_cache/.
  5. FanGraphs              ISO, wOBA, K%, wRC+, zone contact rate.
                            Cached 24h in .stat_cache/.
  6. MLB Stats API          Confirmed lineups, batting order, probable pitchers,
                            schedule. Free, no key needed.

  8. PropLine               Implied run totals fallback (when FL unavailable).
  9. Open-Meteo             Live weather fallback (when FL weather unavailable).

SCORING MODEL
-------------
  Batter Power     Barrel%, HardHit%, ISO, EV, SweetSpot% vs league avg
  Pitcher Vuln     ERA, HR/9, Barrel% allowed, HardHit% allowed (Savant)
  Pitch Matchup    L/R handedness split advantage
  Park Factor      HR-adjusted (Coors=1.38, Petco=0.88, etc.)
  Environment      Temp, wind speed/direction, dome adjustment
  Lineup Spot      Estimated PA/game from batting order position
  Implied Runs     Vegas team run total — boosts power hitters on high-total teams
  Form Factor      Recent 15-game vs full-season stat weighting

OUTPUT
------
  Excel workbook auto-saved to:
    C:\\Users\\hlee145\\Documents\\FanDuel Spreadsheets\\HR Models\\hr_model_YYYY-MM-DD.xlsx
  4 tabs: 🏆 Rankings | 📊 Detailed Stats | ⚾ Pitchers | 🌤️ Game Context

CACHING
-------
  Stat caches (Savant, FanGraphs, bullpen) refresh every 4-24h automatically.
  Odds/props cache locks once all lineups are confirmed (no wasted API calls).
  Use --refresh-odds to force a new fetch if needed.
  Weather cache refreshes every 4h.

MANUAL OVERRIDES
----------------
  Edit the MANUAL OVERRIDES section at the bottom of this file to lock
  specific players, adjust split factors, or override projections.

INSTALL DEPENDENCIES (once)
----------------------------
  pip install pybaseball openpyxl pandas numpy tqdm requests sports-odds-api
"""

